

The Peruvian government signed several deals on Tuesday with China and Japan on cooperation in the fields of mining, geology and energy, local press reported on Tuesday.

Peru's official Institute of Geology, Mining and Metallurgy (IGMMP) signed a memorandum of understanding on exchanging scientists and cooperating with China's geological service in the fields of mining and geology.

The Ministry of Energy and Mines signed a deal with the Japanese International Cooperation Agency to boost rural electrification, particularly with resort to renewable energies like solar energy, wind power, hydro-electric power and geothermal energy.

